com.amitinside.featureflags.listener

Interface ConfigurationListener

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Consumer<ConfigurationEvent>
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface ConfigurationListener
extends Consumer<ConfigurationEvent>
    Listener for Configuration Events. When a ConfigurationEvent is fired, it is asynchronously delivered to all ConfigurationListeners.

    ConfigurationListener objects are registered with the Framework service registry and are notified with a ConfigurationEvent object when an event is fired.

    ConfigurationListener objects can inspect the received ConfigurationEvent object to determine several properties.

    This interface is intended to be implemented by feature providers.
